This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with the task of textual response generation in a multimodal dialogue system. It also involves the use of natural language processing techniques such as the Hierarchical Recurrent Encoder-Decoder (HRED) model. 

The paper also involves the use of computer vision techniques as it deals with a multimodal dataset in the fashion domain. Therefore, it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). 

Additionally, the paper involves the use of machine learning techniques such as deep learning to improve the performance of the dialogue system. Therefore, it could also belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
